gunship and includes audio of military radio

00:38:23.840 --> 00:38:31.050
transmissions. Two Reuter’s employees, a
photographer, and his driver were killed in

00:38:31.050 --> 00:38:35.990
the attack along with at least eight other
people, and two children were seriously injured.

00:38:35.990 --> 00:38:40.400
The radio transmissions show not only the
utter callousness of the soldiers, laughing

00:38:40.400 --> 00:38:46.350
and swearing as they kill, but also the strict
procedure they follow ensuring that all of

00:38:46.350 --> 00:38:51.080
their attacks are clearly authorized by their
chain of command. They don't just open fire;

00:38:51.080 --> 00:38:57.270
they always ask for permission. The leaked
video is a grim depiction of how routine the

00:38:57.270 --> 00:39:02.391
killing of civilians has become, and it's
a stark reminder of how necessary journalism

00:39:02.391 --> 00:39:09.400
is and how dangerous its practice has become.
The photographer, Namir Noor-Eldeen, was 22

00:39:09.400 --> 00:39:16.800
years old. His driver was Saeed Chmagh. He
was 40. Reuters demanded a full investigation.

00:39:16.800 --> 00:39:22.230
Noor-Eldeen, despite his youth, had been described
by colleagues of one of the pre-eminent war

00:39:22.230 --> 00:39:28.010
photographers in Iraq. Chmagh was a family,
was a father of four. The video shows a group

00:39:28.010 --> 00:39:33.350
