and it was November 12th, 1991. The Indonesian

00:59:09.410 --> 00:59:13.840
military occupied the whole island. The people
were holding a procession for a young man

00:59:13.840 --> 00:59:17.890
who had been killed two weeks before. There
were thousands of Timorese. They were at the

00:59:17.890 --> 00:59:21.190
cemetery; it was about 8 o’clock in the
morning. We were interviewing people. This

00:59:21.190 --> 00:59:25.250
was a land where there was no freedom of press,
no freedom of speech, no freedom of assembly,

00:59:25.250 --> 00:59:31.440
and yet they marched to the cemetery putting
up their hands in the “V” sign saying,

00:59:31.440 --> 00:59:38.050
“Viva East Timor, viva independence!”
And soldiers marched up on them, 10 to 12

00:59:38.050 --> 00:59:44.590
abreast, holding their U.S. M-16s at the ready
position. Alan and I thought maybe if we walked

00:59:44.590 --> 00:59:50.000
to the front of the crowd they would not commit
a massacre because, though we knew they committed

00:59:50.000 --> 00:59:53.480
many, they had never done it in front of western
journalists. We always hid our equipment,

00:59:53.480 --> 00:59:58.040
but this time we put on headphones. I held
up my microphone like a flag. I slung my radio

00:59:58.040 --> 01:00:02.490
and my tape recorder over my shoulder. Alan
put the camera above his head. We walked to

01:00:02.490 --> 01:00:06.980
the front of the crowd. The soldiers marched
up, they swept around the corner, they swept

01:00:06.980 --> 01:00:11.310
passed us. And without warning, without hesitation,
without provocation they opened fire on the

01:00:11.310 --> 01:00:15.550
crowd gunning people down from right to left.
The first to go down, a little boy behind

01:00:15.550 --> 01:00:21.270
us putting his hands up in the V sign, exploded
from the gun fire. The soldiers went after

01:00:21.270 --> 01:00:25.750
us, a group of them; they brought me down,
beating me. Alan got a photograph of them

01:00:25.750 --> 01:00:30.520
opening fire on the crowd and then he threw
himself on top of me to protect me from further

01:00:30.520 --> 01:00:34.700
injury. And they took their US M16's like
baseball bats and they slammed them against

01:00:34.700 --> 01:00:40.100
his skull until they fractured it. So we were
laying on the ground, he was covered in blood,

01:00:40.100 --> 01:00:44.800
they were killing everyone around us, and
a group of soldiers put the guns to our heads.

01:00:44.800 --> 01:00:52.800
Our guns, US M16's. Umm, and they were shouting
Polotic in Australia. Polotic, they were saying.

01:00:52.800 --> 01:00:59.780
It was political to witness this, for us to
witness this. But that's our jobs as journalists,

01:00:59.780 --> 01:01:04.350
to go to where the silence is. And they were
shouting Australia because they were demanding

01:01:04.350 --> 01:01:10.140
to know if were from Australia. That's because
seventeen years before when Indonesia invaded,

01:01:10.140 --> 01:01:14.520
umm... there were five Australian based journalists
covering the invasion. They lined them up

01:01:14.520 --> 01:01:19.130
against a house, the Indonesian soldiers and
they executed them all. The sixth, Roger East,

01:01:19.130 --> 01:01:23.430
was reporting from a radio station in Dili,
the capital of Timor, the day after the invasion.

01:01:23.430 --> 01:01:28.000
They dragged him out of the radio station
and as he shouted "I'm from Australia!" they

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:34.420
shot him into the harbor with thousands of
Timorese and killed him. Umm...so the Australian

01:01:34.420 --> 01:01:39.310
government hardly protested their killings.
We believe because years later Australia and

01:01:39.310 --> 01:01:44.970
Indonesia would sign the Timor Gap Treaty
dividing up Timor's oil between Australia

01:01:44.970 --> 01:01:50.170
and Indonesia. Oil is the source of so much
pain in the world. So as we lay on the ground,

01:01:50.170 --> 01:01:54.400
Alan covered in blood, the soldiers with their
guns at our heads at the ready position, at

01:01:54.400 --> 01:02:00.810
the ready position, umm...we shouted back
"America!" They stripped us now of everything.

01:02:00.810 --> 01:02:05.530
The only thing I had left was my passport,
and I threw it at them as we shouted "America!”

01:02:05.530 --> 01:02:09.980
I get kicked in the stomach. When I get my
breath back, I'd say "America!” And at some

01:02:09.980 --> 01:02:14.770
point they pulled the guns from our heads.
We believe because we were from the same country

01:02:14.770 --> 01:02:18.900
their weapons were from. They would have to
pay a price for killing us that they would

01:02:18.900 --> 01:02:24.560
never had to pay for killing the Timorese.
They killed more than 270 Timorese on that

01:02:24.560 --> 01:02:33.210
one day. And that was not one of the larger
massacres. So, when Alan stood up to ask Kissinger

01:02:33.210 --> 01:02:40.890
