on CNN to, you know, responded to, it was

01:12:17.170 --> 01:12:21.850
the day that President and Mrs. Obama went
to the White House to meet with the Bush's.

01:12:21.850 --> 01:12:26.920
You know he was selected but they weren't
yet moving in. And so it was in the afternoon.

01:12:26.920 --> 01:12:31.760
I was sitting in the CNN studios, and they
were chattering about something, and then

01:12:31.760 --> 01:12:35.960
the Obamas were walking into the White House,
and they asked me about something else. I

01:12:35.960 --> 01:12:43.440
said, “No, wait, wait. We have to take pause.
I mean, look at what's happening right now.

01:12:43.440 --> 01:12:51.310
Barack Hussein Obama, Michelle LaVaughn Robinson
Obama are walking into the White House in

01:12:51.310 --> 01:12:58.010
which they will live. Michelle LaVaughn Robinson
Obama, her grandfather comes from South Carolina.

01:12:58.010 --> 01:13:01.990
They are the descendants of slaves which means
their children, Malia and Sascha, are the

01:13:01.990 --> 01:13:06.360
descendants of slaves, and they will live
in the White House. The most famous house

01:13:06.360 --> 01:13:12.560
in the world that was built by slaves. Let's
take pause.”

01:13:12.560 --> 01:13:22.260
Now, what about all of the policies in the
last year? Particularly, the surge in Afghanistan?

01:13:22.260 --> 01:13:28.760
President Obama making Bush's war Obama's
war? Receiving the Nobel Peace Prize as he

01:13:28.760 --> 01:13:37.230
announces the surge? Talking about Dr. King,
I think six times in that Nobel acceptance

01:13:37.230 --> 01:13:44.930
speech. Dr. King, who on April 4th, 1967,
a year to the day before he was assassinated,

01:13:44.930 --> 01:13:49.930
gave that famous address at Riverside Church.
Even those in his inner circle said, "Don't

01:13:49.930 --> 01:13:53.950
do it. Don’t take on the war in Vietnam.
You've gotten so much for Civil Rights and

01:13:53.950 --> 01:14:00.250
Voting Rights. This is not your issue." And
he said, he talked about the country he loved,

01:14:00.250 --> 01:14:09.910
and he said, "My country is the greatest purveyor
of violence on earth." Dr. King did. And,

01:14:09.910 --> 01:14:15.390
you know, I think for a long time people have
felt in this country that they have hit their

01:14:15.390 --> 01:14:22.750
head against a brick wall. And that brick
wall has now become a door. And the door is

01:14:22.750 --> 01:14:30.830
open a crack. And the question is, will you
kick it open, or will it be slammed shut?

01:14:30.830 --> 01:14:37.060
And I don't think it's up to president Obama.
I think that's up to all of you. I mean, he

01:14:37.060 --> 01:14:45.920
was elected by millions of new voters, especially
young voters, anti-war voters, amazing coalition

01:14:45.920 --> 01:14:55.300
inspired by him. But, I mean, the good thing
is this Community Organizer, the Community

01:14:55.300 --> 01:14:57.660
Organizer and Chief now has become...

01:14:57.660 --> 01:15:03.150
Well, the Community Organizer first, let me
address that one. That’s an amazing thing.

01:15:03.150 --> 01:15:08.490
So now parents all over the country are saying
to their kids, “Maybe you can be a Community

01:15:08.490 --> 01:15:13.520
Organizer too.” That's pretty amazing. But
the Community Organizer and Chief has become

01:15:13.520 --> 01:15:18.170
the Commander and Chief. And who is going
to do the community organizing now? And that's

01:15:18.170 --> 01:15:25.730
up to all of you. Maybe the answer is in something
in Obama once said. I heard the story. I wasn't

01:15:25.730 --> 01:15:32.720
there, but a year and a half before the election
he was campaigning in New Jersey, and he was

01:15:32.720 --> 01:15:37.860
at one of these fundraisers in the backyard
of a house in Montclair, New Jersey. And people

01:15:37.860 --> 01:15:41.070
were asking him questions. He was about to
go, and this guy raises his hand and said,

01:15:41.070 --> 01:15:50.170
"What about the Middle East?" And Obama related
the story of, ah, A. Phillip Randolph, the

01:15:50.170 --> 01:15:53.500
greatest Community Organizer of the twentieth
century. You know, he organized the Brotherhood

01:15:53.500 --> 01:15:58.910
of Sleeping Car Porters, the black porters
on the Pullman trains. He organized the 1963

01:15:58.910 --> 01:16:05.960
march on Washington. And Eleanor Roosevelt
took A. Phillip Randolph to meet F.D.R. and

01:16:05.960 --> 01:16:11.190
A. Phillip Randolph said to F.D.R., talked
about the condition of black people in this

01:16:11.190 --> 01:16:15.470
country and working people in this country.
And F.D.R., this is the story Obama told,

01:16:15.470 --> 01:16:20.560
F.D.R. turned to A. Phillip Randolph and said,
"I don't disagree with anything that you’re

01:16:20.560 --> 01:16:27.190
saying, but you've got to make me do it. Make
me do it.” And that's what Obama said on

01:16:27.190 --> 01:16:31.790
the issue of the Middle East. "Make me do
it". And I really think that's what democracy

01:16:31.790 --> 01:16:37.920
is all about. If you feel strongly about something,
about the critical issues of the day, you

01:16:37.920 --> 01:16:39.300
gotta make him do it.

01:16:39.300 --> 01:16:43.150
Katina Johnson:
All right. I just want to say thanks so much

01:16:43.150 --> 01:16:45.760
for what you do. It's deeply needed, and thanks
for coming today.

01:16:45.760 --> 01:16:47.210
Amy Goodman:
Thank you very much.

